---
import ProductLayout from '@/layouts/ProductLayout.astro';
---

<ProductLayout
  title="BSGateway — Smart LLM Routing"
  description="Stop choosing models. The right one is picked for you."
  locale="en"
  product="BSGateway"
  accent="#f59e0b"
  appUrl="https://gateway.bsvibe.dev"
>
  <h1>BSGateway</h1>
  <p class="product-tagline">Stop choosing models. BSGateway automatically routes your requests to the optimal LLM based on cost, performance, and availability.</p>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>

  <div class="feature-grid">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Smart Routing</h3>
      <p>Analyzes request characteristics and automatically selects the best model from GPT-4, Claude, Gemini, and more.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Cost Optimization</h3>
      <p>Lightweight models for simple tasks, premium models for complex ones. Reduce per-token costs by up to 90%.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Fallback Chains</h3>
      <p>Automatic failover when a provider goes down. Zero downtime, seamless reliability.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Usage Analytics</h3>
      <p>Real-time tracking of usage and costs by model, task type, and time period.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>OpenAI-Compatible API</h2>
  <p>Start without changing a single line of code. Just update your base URL and BSGateway handles the rest.</p>

  <h2>Use Cases</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Startups</strong> — Maximum performance on a limited budget with automatic cost optimization</li>
    <li><strong>Agencies</strong> — Different clients, different needs. Set routing policies per project</li>
    <li><strong>Enterprise</strong> — Multi-provider strategy. Flexible infrastructure without vendor lock-in</li>
  </ul>
</ProductLayout>
